video.title: Big Time Rush
video.synopsis: After a talent agent discovers four talented pals and turns them into a boy band called Big Time Rush, they must adjust to their exciting new lives.

episodes.synopsis: Four musically talented best friends — Kendall, James, Logan and Carlos — hit it big after a famous record producer discovers them in an audition.
episodes.title: Big Time Audition

episodes.synopsis: The guys get a dose of reality when Gustavo tells them they have to go to school while they live in Los Angeles.
episodes.title: Big Time School of Rocque

episodes.synopsis: The guys aren't thrilled with their boring apartment at the Palm Woods, and they hatch a plan to improve it.
episodes.title: Big Time Crib

episodes.synopsis: The record company CEO thinks adding a fifth band member will broaden Big Time Rush's appeal and sticks the guys with a self-proclaimed "bad boy."
episodes.title: Big Time Bad Boy

episodes.synopsis: The guys all chase the same girl, causing problems in the band for the first time.
episodes.title: Big Time Love Song

episodes.synopsis: When Gustavo has to go away on business, he lets the guys house-sit his mansion.
episodes.title: Big Time Mansion

episodes.synopsis: The pressure is on as the guys prepare for their first band photo, which could land them in all the teen magazines.
episodes.title: Big Time Photo Shoot

episodes.synopsis: Spending all their time together has given the guys cabin fever, so they decide to spend some time apart.
episodes.title: Big Time Break

episodes.synopsis: It's been three months since the boys moved to Hollywood to record their demo. Now it's up to Griffin to decide the future of the band.
episodes.title: Big Time Demos

episodes.synopsis: When Gustavo excludes the boys from his studio party, they throw a small get-together of their own, but things get totally out of control.
episodes.title: Big Time Party

episodes.synopsis: The boys get jobs to pay off their debt with Gustavo.
episodes.title: Big Time Jobs

episodes.synopsis: Gustavo moves in with the guys when his mansion gets flooded. Meanwhile, there's a ghost haunting the Palm Woods.
episodes.title: Big Time Blogger

episodes.synopsis: The boys do everything in their power to prove to Hollywood's top entertainment blogger that they're not big-time phonies!
episodes.title: Big Time Terror

episodes.synopsis: The boys are responsible for planning the end-of-the-year party and performing at the event. Can they get their act together in time?
episodes.title: Big Time Dance

episodes.synopsis: Jordin Sparks is staying at the Palm Woods while recording a new song with Gustavo. The guys are told to stay away from her because they're bad luck.
episodes.title: Big Time Sparks

episodes.synopsis: When James, Carlos and Logan catch Hollywood fever and start acting weird, it's up to Kendall to figure out how to cure them.
episodes.title: Big Time Fever

episodes.synopsis: The guys promise Camille and a whole bunch of other people roles in their upcoming music video. But Gustavo says no way!
episodes.title: Big Time Video

episodes.synopsis: Griffin informs the boys that their album and concert have been canceled. But when the boys return to Minnesota, they take matters into their own hands.
episodes.title: Big Time Concert

episodes.synopsis: The boys return from tour and find Jo flirting with a hot new guy, new kids hanging out at the pool ... and loads of schoolwork!
episodes.title: Welcome Back Big Time

episodes.synopsis: The guys are visited by their hometown friend who happens to be an awesome singer ... but also the world's biggest klutz!
episodes.title: Big Time Fans

episodes.synopsis: James helps Camille run lines for an audition and they end up kissing! Meanwhile, Gustavo tries to set up Carlos with his first girlfriend.
episodes.title: Big Time Girlfriends

episodes.synopsis: The boys are scheduled to make their first TV appearance, but when it looks like they'll be bumped, they do whatever it takes to keep their spot.
episodes.title: Big Time Live

episodes.synopsis: The monstrous personas of Big Time Rush come to light: James is a sexy vampire, Logan is a zombie, Carlos is Franken-Carlos and Kendall is a werewolf.
episodes.title: Big Time Halloween

episodes.synopsis: Jo's publicist wants the press to think she's dating her new co-star, so Kendall and Jo must sneak around and hide their relationship.
episodes.title: Big Time Sneakers

episodes.synopsis: It's the annual Day of Pranks competition at the Palm Woods, and soon a boys vs. girls prank war erupts!
episodes.title: Big Time Pranks

episodes.synopsis: Gustavo gets a spiritual guru to help him with his anger issues, but the guru talks Gustavo into letting him run Rocque Records.
episodes.title: Big Time Guru

episodes.synopsis: The guys record a last-minute Christmas EP with Miranda Cosgrove and others. But by the time they're done, it may be too late to catch their flight.
episodes.title: Big Time Christmas

episodes.synopsis: Kendall and Jo help Carlos find a date, and Logan flirts with a new girl while still confused about his feelings for Camille.
episodes.title: Big Time Crush

episodes.synopsis: Determined to get more involved with the recording process, the boys compete to write a new song for BTR.
episodes.title: Big Time Songwriters

episodes.synopsis: The group hangs out at Griffin's beach house for the day. Carlos and Logan hunt for buried treasure, and James falls for a girl he thinks is a mermaid.
episodes.title: Big Time Beach Party

episodes.synopsis: Gustavo starts an all-girl pop group, sparking jealousy from the guys.
episodes.title: Big Time Girl Group

episodes.synopsis: Griffin films the guys' lives for a reality show. All of them (except James) are reluctant to participate.
episodes.title: Big Time Reality

episodes.synopsis: James's mom, nicknamed the "Estée Lauder of the Midwest," arrives to bring James home and groom him to take over the family business.
episodes.title: Big Time Moms

episodes.synopsis: When Jo gets offered the role of a lifetime, she must chose between her career and her relationship with Kendall.
episodes.title: Big Time Break-Up

episodes.synopsis: There's a school project to make Palm Woods "go green." The competition heats when the students learn there's a prize: a whole week off of school!
episodes.title: Green Time Rush

episodes.synopsis: James's fairy-tale romance with a foreign princess quickly becomes an escape mission after he inadvertently proposes marriage.
episodes.title: Big Time Wedding

episodes.synopsis: It's prom time, and the guys are all scrambling to win the coveted title of Prom King!
episodes.title: Big Time Prom Kings

episodes.synopsis: A teen magazine runs a "Win a Date with BTR" contest, and the four winning girls, each with her own baggage, give the guys serious dating drama.
episodes.title: Big Time Contest

episodes.synopsis: A new rocker-chick neighbor blows the guys away. Carlos and James are desperate to date her, while Kendall tries to prove that BTR can rock too.
episodes.title: Big Time Rocker

episodes.synopsis: BTR refuses to record their second album after Gustavo is too hard on them, and the strike pits the band against their producer in a battle of wills.
episodes.title: Big Time Strike

episodes.synopsis: While Gustavo struggles to write the band's next hit song, the guys try to cheer up Kendall, who is heartbroken after his break-up with Jo.
episodes.title: Big Time Single

episodes.synopsis: Hawk has returned and has a new evil plan to take down Big Time Rush. He plans on stealing BTR's new tracks and releasing them himself!
episodes.title: Big Time Superheroes

episodes.synopsis: Kendall and Camille are spending lots of time together, making Logan suspicious. James reveals to Carlos that Carlos's camp crush liked him back.
episodes.title: Big Time Secret

episodes.synopsis: The boys have a fight and decide to move out. James ends up squatting in a cool retiree's apartment, while Logan moves to a place by the water.
episodes.title: Big Time Move

episodes.synopsis: Big Time Rush has dropped their second album, and a TV program has the guys making revealing comments about their lives inside and outside the band.
episodes.title: Big Time Interview

episodes.synopsis: On the last stop of the group's world tour, footage provides highlights from a live concert, spirited high jinks and all the drama behind the curtain.
episodes.title: Backstage Rush

episodes.synopsis: The boys return from their vacation and are now famous in Palm Woods, but all they want is to have fun and meet girls; Griffin tries to bribe Carlos.
episodes.title: Big Time Returns

episodes.synopsis: The group is too famous to live in Palm Woods, so they move to Bel Air. But the boys don't like the rules that come with a life of luxury.
episodes.title: Bel Air Rush

episodes.synopsis: James helps Carlos with his date with one of the Jennifers, Kendall has dinner with Lucy and her parents, and Logan goes on a blind date.
episodes.title: Big Time Double Date

episodes.synopsis: Griffin offers a line of promotional goods to the CEO of Selmart, but the boys hate the products and decide to take matters into their own hands.
episodes.title: Big Time Merchandise

episodes.synopsis: Kendall and Lucy are about to share their first kiss when Lucy's ex-boyfriend intervenes; Griffin recruits Logan and Carlos for corporate espionage.
episodes.title: Big Time Surprise

episodes.synopsis: Kendall plans to ask Lucy out, but when Jo shows up, he has to choose between the two girls. Carlos and James's friendship is put to the test.
episodes.title: Big Time Decision

episodes.synopsis: Kendall and Logan have to take care of Roque Records's new artist, an eccentric rock legend, until his induction into the Rock & Roll Hall of Fame.
episodes.title: Big Time Babysitting

episodes.synopsis: When Gustavo thinks it's too dangerous for the boys to go camping, they try to camp out in the sound booth, but roughing it isn't their strongpoint.
episodes.title: Big Time Camping

episodes.synopsis: Kendall and Logan volunteer at a dog shelter and end up adopting 12 dogs; Carlos and Jennifer's love of puppies gets out of hand.
episodes.title: Big Time Rescue

episodes.synopsis: Kendall buys Jo a necklace to show his commitment, but Camille believes that Logan bought it for her; Gustavo hangs up the band's new gold record.
episodes.title: Big Time Gold

episodes.synopsis: The kids take desperate measures when they accidentally ruin the tape of the episode of "Big Time Rush" that they're due to deliver to the channel.
episodes.title: Big Time Bloopers

episodes.synopsis: The boys try to hire a new manager when they feel threatened by a new wave of British pop bands but can't agree on who should replace Gustavo.
episodes.title: Big Time Invasion

episodes.synopsis: Lucy's revenge album about Kendall is a big hit; Carlos is accused of hitting an old woman; James spreads a rumor about a duet with Cher Lloyd.
episodes.title: Big Time Scandal

episodes.synopsis: Kendall has to make sure Jo doesn't find out that Lucy has returned to Palm Woods, and Logan's little lie about his illness turns into an emergency.
episodes.title: Big Time Lies

episodes.synopsis: Griffin gives the kids a $20,000 bonus for their good work, but they quickly start making bad decisions with their money and go broke.
episodes.title: Big Time Bonus

episodes.synopsis: BTR makes a guest appearance on a TV show, but Kendall can't act. Carlos is smitten with an actress, and Logan and James fight with Yo Gabba Gabba.
episodes.title: Big Time Cameo

episodes.synopsis: Prank wars break out again in Palm Woods, and the kids take on the adults. In the end, it comes down to Katie, Kendall and Mrs. Knight.
episodes.title: Big Time Pranks II

episodes.synopsis: James continues to woo Lucy by buying a motorcycle; Kendall teaches Jo how to drive a stick shift; Carlos and Logan are attached to an old wagon.
episodes.title: Big Time Rides

episodes.synopsis: Logan brings Carlos to his MCAT exam as a lucky charm, but Carlos gets a better score; James puts his friendship with Kendall to the test.
episodes.title: Big Time Test

episodes.synopsis: BTR looks to expand their brand by becoming a cartoon, but they decide they'd rather be in a video game, which causes them to be mistaken for aliens.
episodes.title: Big Time Cartoon

episodes.synopsis: When somebody tells the boys that groups always break up after their third album, they fight over who's going to break out on a solo career.
episodes.title: Big Time Break Out

episodes.synopsis: BTR is on the tour bus headed to a gig in San Diego but get stuck in traffic due to an accident, so they film a music video while they wait.
episodes.title: Big Time Tour Bus

episodes.synopsis: BTR is slated to perform at the Tween Choice Awards, but a villain bent on brainwashing the crowd may destroy the show — and their dreams.
episodes.title: Big Time Dreams
